{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/solar-arbitrage-the-real-estate-and-clean-energy-opportunity-d0ff08e4152", "time": 1683008022.516758, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/solar-arbitrage-the-real-estate-and-clean-energy-opportunity-d0ff08e4152/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "The Solar Energy and Real Estate Sustainability Business Opportunity | by Allen Jiang | Towards Data Science", "h1": "The Solar Energy and Real Estate Sustainability Business Opportunity", "description": "The world population is increasing from 7.8 billion today, to a projected 12 billion over the next 50 years. That\u2019s 4.2 billion new people on the planet, which is ~13x the size of USA. To sustain\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["The world population is increasing from 7.8 billion today, to a projected 12 billion over the next 50 years. That\u2019s 4.2 billion new people on the planet, which is ~13x the size of USA.", "To sustain this growth, we need to produce more energy. But to sustain the Earth, we need sustainable energy. So then the question becomes: is there a way to solve these problems while creating a profitable business?", "The above is a map of solar irradiance, which is the power per unit area (watt per square metre, W/m2) received from the sun.", "The business case: Australia is one of the largest land masses with the highest amounts of solar irradiance on the planet, but have its land prices accounted for the value of sunlight exposure? The opportunity is to find undervalued land with significant exposure to sunlight and turn that land primarily into a solar farm \u2014 a business case for Solar Arbitrage.", "The business model comes from selling electricity back into the grid and creating both B2C and B2B energy solutions. This could be selling electricity back to Australia, Singapore, providing cheaper electricity for consumers, and creating B2B energy solutions like Tesla\u2019s Powerpack & Megapack.", "Utilizing data science, let\u2019s explore if this opportunity exists. What we are looking for: a location in Australia where there is the highest ratio of sunlight exposure to cheap land.", "There is no publicly available data on this (hence the \u2018secret\u2019 opportunity) so we have to manually piece the puzzles together. The key variables of interest: location, land size, price, annual solar exposure. Data sources:", "Much of the work is in gathering the data and calculating the solar to land price ratio, which has been done in this data set. We are looking for large amounts of land, such as rural and farm land.", "The key column here is \u201cSolar / Price Per Sq Metre\u201d, which is the amount of solar exposure this land gets for every $1. The higher the number, the better profit opportunity.", "Let\u2019s check if there is currently a correlation between Price / SqMetre and Solar Exposure? In other words, does the current real estate market price account for solar exposure?", "It does not seem like current real estate prices reflect solar exposure. This is perhaps where the opportunity is! Next, let\u2019s visualize the locations. Here\u2019s where Python beats Excel. We will plot the locations and give each a weighting based on their Solar / Price Per Sq Metre ratio.", "The takeaway: not too far from the Great Barrier Reef in Queensland Australia, would be the ideal location to build a profitable solar farm.", "This initial exploration shows the potential Real Estate and Clean Energy Opportunity and its worthiness for deeper analysis. The next steps would be to expand the dataset into a full list of locations and to explore the business model of building a solar farm. Some questions would include: what would be the cost of building and maintaining a large solar farm, how much energy can be created and what are the profit margins, what other opportunities are there for that land use? In what other locations worldwide does this opportunity also exist?", "Like food, energy is an essential part of human life. The need for energy will always exist and into the future, the demands for energy will continue to increase. This is a real opportunity to do good in a profitable way.", "If this has sparked some curiosity, let\u2019s connect. I\u2019d love to explore this further.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Writing to preserve and evolve knowledge."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fd0ff08e4152&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsolar-arbitrage-the-real-estate-and-clean-energy-opportunity-d0ff08e4152&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsolar-arbitrage-the-real-estate-and-clean-energy-opportunity-d0ff08e4152&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsolar-arbitrage-the-real-estate-and-clean-energy-opportunity-d0ff08e4152&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_t